Dr. Jill Biden, the wife of former Vice President Joe Biden, will lead a Presidential Delegation to the 2011 Special Olympics World Summer Games in Athens, Greece. The delegation will participate in various events, including the lighting of the Flame of Hope, the Opening Ceremonies, and the Special Olympics Aquatic Competition. They will also attend a dedication ceremony for the naming of the Eunice Kennedy Shriver Square. Dr. Biden will also meet with staff and families at the U.S. Embassy in Athens and visit the USS Ramage to thank sailors for their service. The delegation will include several notable individuals, such as the U.S. Ambassador to the Hellenic Republic, the Assistant Secretary for Educational and Cultural Affairs, and members of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities.